cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.AR 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with generating high-quality random numbers using PRNG methods in the category of block and stream ciphers. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it showcases the scalability and performance of the proposed method in a parallel GPU implementation. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it employs a bitsliced data representation as building blocks of algorithms. It may also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it discusses the alteration of the paradigm of internal functions and data structure in the implementation of the MICKEY 2.0 PRNG. Finally, it may belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it discusses the suitability of the LFSR-based nature of the PRNG in the implementation for GPU's many-core structure.
